### **`README.md`**\
```markdown\
# NaveScript (NvS)\
\
[![Go Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/Go-1.22-blue.svg)](https://golang.org)\
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green.svg)](LICENSE)\
[![Documentation](https://img.shields.io/badge/docs-navescript.org-blue)](https://navescript.org)\
[![Build Status](https://github.com/navescript/nvs/workflows/CI/badge.svg)](https://github.com/navescript/nvs/actions)\
\
**NaveScript** is a modern, fast, and expressive programming language with built-in concurrency, polyglot support, and a rich standard library.\
\
## \uc0\u10024  Features\
\
- \uc0\u55357 \u56960  **Blazing Fast** - JIT compilation and optimized bytecode VM\
- \uc0\u55357 \u56580  **Built-in Concurrency** - Goroutines and channels\
- \uc0\u55357 \u56588  **Polyglot** - Call Python, JS, C, and Rust code\
- \uc0\u55356 \u57263  **Type Safety** - Optional static typing with inference\
- \uc0\u55356 \u57104  **WebAssembly** - Compile NvS to WASM\
- \uc0\u55357 \u57056 \u65039  **Complete Tooling** - Package manager, debugger, profiler\
\
## \uc0\u55357 \u56550  Installation\
\
### macOS\
```bash\
brew install navescript/nvs/nvs\
```\
\
### Linux\
```bash\
curl -fsSL https://navescript.org/install.sh | bash\
```\
\
### Windows\
```bash\
winget install NaveScript.NVS\
